            <div>
                <opener><dateline>March. 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775.</dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>as I have one more Frank I shall forbear this post <persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Jacksonâ€™s</persName> indulgence. It is pity
                    the author of the antiquities of <placeName ref="pl0235">Sterling</placeName> does not print them separate.<note type="editorial">Originally printed as a series in <bibl type="editorial"><title ref="bi0076"><hi rend="italic">The Edinburgh Magazine and
                                    Review</hi></title></bibl> from 1773 and 1774, William Nimmo's
                        'Antiquities in Stirlingshire' would eventually be published separately as
                            <bibl type="editorial"><title ref="bi0136"><hi rend="italic">A general
                                    history of Stirlingshire</hi></title> (1777)</bibl>.</note> I am
                    pleased with the remarks on <persName ref="pe0073">Johnson</persName> but shall
                    make no use of them; nor shall I once mention him; for really he is not worth
                        notice.<note type="editorial">Pennant may be referring to a recent
                        contribution to <hi rend="italic">The St. James Chronicle</hi> for 18
                        February 1775. Entitled <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0190">'Sketch
                                of a Comparison between the two late Writers of Travels in
                                SCOTLAND'</title></bibl> and signed 'STAFFA', the piece favourably
                        compares Pennant's account of Scotland to Johnson's.</note> Be so good as to
                    forward the inclosed.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> most obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>. Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pat<gap reason="damage" unit="lines" atLeast="2" atMost="3"/></addrLine>
                    </address></p>
                <p>FreeR<gap reason="damage" unit="words" atLeast="1" atMost="2"/></p>
                <p><stamp type="handstamp"><placeName ref="pl0703">NORTHOP</placeName></stamp></p>
            </div>
